text: Tyson Beukeboom (born March 10, 1991) is a Canadian rugby union player. She represented at the 2014 Women's Rugby World Cup. She made her debut at the 2013 Nations Cup. Beukeboom attended St. Francis Xavier University. In 2012, she was named the CIS Female Athlete of the Year. Beukeboom is the daughter of former ice hockey player Jeff Beukeboom. ==References== ==External links== * Rugby Canada Player Profile Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian female rugby union players Category:Canadian people of Dutch descent Category:Sportspeople from Edmonton
